place.name: THELVETON
place.gazetteerText: THELVETON, or Thelton, a parish in Depwade district, Norfolk; 2 miles NE of Diss r. station. Post town, Scole. Acres, 1,050. Real property, £1,709. Pop., 160. Houses, 31. T. Hall is the seat of T. Havers, Esq. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £249.* Patron, the Lord Chancellor. The church was recently repaired. A Roman Catholic chapel is at T. Hall. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
